headline: As US blows up drug boats, Venezuelan oil sets sail
summary: While the American military blows up boats it claims are transporting drugs from Venezuela, observers say tankers shipping Venezuelan oil in violation of a US embargo continue to navigate the very same Caribbean waters undisturbed.US strikes on alleged drug-carrying boats in the Caribbean and eastern Pacific -- in violation of international law according to human rights experts -- have so far claimed at least 57 lives.
